<paragraph blockId="78.[151,1436,1812,2019]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">
The 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1853" box="[205,356,1812,1838]" class="Insecta" family="Dicteriadidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Dicteriadidae</taxonomicName>
contains only two monotypic genera. They are large to medium-sized damselflies that perch with the wings held out horizontally; the legs are very long and slender without conspicuous setae. Only one genus occurs in 
<collectingCountry box="[260,356,1884,1910]" name="Ecuador" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
